==English==
===Etymology===
[L. adaptare; ad + aptare to fit; cf. F. adapter. See {Apt}, {Adept}.]

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ʌ.dæptˈ/

===Adjective===
#Fitted; suited.

===Translations===
*[[Albanian]]: adapt
*Finnish: [[sopiva]]

===Verb (transitive)===
[imp. & p. p. {Adapted}; p. pr. & vb. n. {Adapting}.] 
#To make suitable; to fit, or suit; to adjust; to alter so as to fit for a new use; &mdash; sometimes followed by to or for.

